('483', 'For more information about admission, please see\nwww.abs.uva.nl/mif\nwww.studeren.uva.nl/mif.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'admission', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('483', 'To provide intensive training in international finance. Students are prepared for international careers dealing with issues in corporate finance, investment banking, risk management and international economics. Option to specialise in either corporat', 'e finance or mathematical finance.', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('483', 'Advanced Corporate Finance & Valuation, Investments, Financial Econometrics, International Financial Management, M&A, Restructuring and Corporate Governance, Financial Derivatives, Risk Management & Financial Institutions, Financial Modelling.\nFor mo', 're information about the courses for 2011-2012, please see www.studeren.uva.nl/english_mif.', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('483', 'Interactive lectures, case studies, group assignments and presentations, thesis.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'instruction modes', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('483', 'The deadline to be eligible for the early-bird tuition fee of  23,000 is March 1, 2012.\nThe deadline to receive a 5% discount if you pay your tuition fee at once is April 30, 2012.\nThe deadline to be eligible for the MIF Tuition Waiver Scheme is M', 'ay 31, 2012.\nApplication deadline for candidates who need to complete the MIF Pre-Course Training is May 31, 2012.\nTuition fees are adjusted annually. For up-to-date information, please see www.uva.nl/isp.\n\n', 'NULL', 'website', 'tuition fee', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('483', 'The GMAT or GRE is compulsory for all applicants to the full-time programme. Applicants with a PhD may apply for an exemption. We require a minimum GMAT score of around 630 and a minimum analytical writing score of around 4.0. The required minimum GR', 'E score is around 650 (quantitative) and around 4.0 for analytical writing (the combined score should be 1200 or higher). If you apply to the part-time programme you can opt to take our in-house test as a substitute for the GMAT or GRE.', 'NULL', 'website', 'admission', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('483', 'The programme is ideal for those seeking a career in finance and for established finance professionals who are looking to enhance their career prospects. Graduates go on to work in areas that require thorough understanding of the complexities of inte', 'rnational finance, such as asset management, corporate finance, project finance and treasury. Graduates often pursue careers in international organisations.', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('483', 'For more information about the courses for 2011-2012, please see: \nwww.abs.uva.nl/mif\nwww.studeren.uva.nl/mif.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('485', 'Als breed-opgeleide academicus heb je daarom een belangrijke meerwaarde. Je bent inzetbaar in sectoren waar je een kritische, zelfstandige geest nodig hebt zoals de journalistiek, de politiek of het (hoger)onderwijs. Denk ook aan functies op het gebi', 'ed van duurzaamheid en innovatie.\n\n', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('486', 'The MSc Accountancy & Control has two tracks, one in accountancy and one in controlling.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('486', 'IFRS 1 (5 EC),\nManagement Control (5 EC),\nSustainability, Accountability and Ethics (5 EC),\nInternal Control & Accounting Information Systems (5 EC),\nResearch Seminar Accountancy & Control (5 EC),\nCorporate Governance and Risk Management (5 EC),\nFina', 'ncial Accounting Research (5 EC),\nIFRS 2 (5 EC),\nAssurance (5 EC),\nMasters Thesis (15 EC).\nFor more information about the courses 2011-2012, please see www.coursecatalogue.uva.nl.', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('486', 'Tuition fees are adjusted annually. For up-to-date information, please see www.uva.nl/isp.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'tuition fee', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('486', 'Positions open to Control graduates vary from controller to financial director. Graduates work for both commercial and nonprofit organisations, as well as for regulatory bodies like the Financial Markets Authority and the Dutch Central Bank. Working ', 'as a controller will appeal to students with a broad interest in issues related to organisation, accounting and financing. Controllers must be able to form and express an opinion about virtually all of an organisation"s activities.', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
