('759', 'The two-year Research Master"s programme in Public International Law aims to give students knowledge and understanding of the fundamental principles of public international law and, in particular, key areas of the international rule of law, legal sci', 'ence and international legal research. At the same time, students will acquire the skills they need to be able to apply their knowledge in these areas in order to conduct fundamental and applied research.', 'NULL', 'website', 'characteristics', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('759', 'Prof. P. A. Nollkaempe:\n"The Research Master in the International Rule of Law deals with some of the most important and fascinating legal topics of our time, such as the world-wide protection of human rights, international criminal justice and the re', 'gulation and control of the powers of the Security Council in maintaining international peace and security. This Master"s will allow students to distinguish themselves in pursuing a career in international law, whether in academia or in practice."\n', 'NULL', 'website', 'international', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('759', 'Please see:\nhttp://www.studeren.uva.nl/rma_public_international_law/object.cfm/9A22153F-1321-B0BE-68190C8619E0465A', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'admission', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('760', 'The Master"s programme in International Criminal Law is the first programme of its kind to focus on international criminal law as a distinct field of legal study.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('760', '12 AC in courses are obtained at Columbia Law School, courses such as Comparative Introduction to American Law. 30 ECTS credits are obtained at Amsterdam Law School, courses such as International Criminal Law, International Criminal Tribunals: Substa', 'ntive Aspects, International Criminal Tribunals: Procedural Aspects and Workshop Prosecution of International Crimes in Practice.', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('760', 'Lectures, seminars, field trips, internships possible', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'instruction modes', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('760', 'Tuition fees are adjusted annually. For up-to-date information, please see www.uva.nl/isp', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'tuition fee', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('760', 'The programme is open to 12 EU nationals applying through the Amsterdam Law School. Students who will obtain their LLB before 1 August, and graduate with at least a 7,5 grade average (on a scale of 1-10) can apply for the programme.  US students shou', 'ld enrol for the programme via Columbia Law School instead.\n\n', 'NULL', 'website', 'admission', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('760', 'The programme prepares students for a career in international criminal law. Graduates will be uniquely qualified to assume leadership roles in the world of international criminal tribunals, such as the ICC, national practice, academia and ministries ', 'of foreign affairs, justice and defence.\n', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('760', 'For application criteria please see:\nhttp://www.studeren.uva.nl/ma_international_criminal_law/object.cfm/9E9745BE-1321-B0BE-A481B37B93079240', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'admission', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('760', 'Amsterdam Law School students and Columbia Law School students complete the programme together, spending the first semester at Columbia Law School, and the second semester at the Amsterdam Law School.\n\n', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'study abroad', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('760', 'This programme is the first of its kind to focus on international criminal law as a distinct field of legal study. The central aim of the programme is to train a new kind of international criminal lawyers who have a broad and deep understanding of in', 'ternational criminal law issues and the academic skills to analyse such issues. The programme incorporates a dual perspective on international criminal law with a focus on common law at Columbia and a focus on civil law at the Amsterdam Law School.\n', 'NULL', 'website', 'characteristics', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('760', 'This joint LLM programme of the Amsterdam Law School and Columbia University School of Law in International Criminal Law is the first of its kind to focus on international criminal law as a distinct field of legal study. The central aim of the progra', 'mme is to train a new kind of international criminal lawyers who have a broad and deep understanding of international criminal law issues and the academic skills to analyse such issues. ', 'NULL', 'website', 'international', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('762', 'Sociaal geografen en planologen doen het prima op de arbeidsmarkt. Mogelijke werkgevers: (milieu)adviesbureaus, beleggers, projectontwikkelaars, vastgoedbedrijven, woningcorporaties, ontwikkelingsorganisaties,\noverheidsinstanties. Zie ook de Carriere', 'krant: http://www.fmg.uva.nl/gpio/actueel.cfm\n\nEen internationale carrire ligt ook binnen de mogelijkheden. Bijvoorbeeld bij een non-gouvernementele organisatie als NOVIB,Plan Nederland of bij de Verenigde Naties.', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('762', 'Volledige informatie over de opleiding en het studieschema:\nhttp://studiegids.uva.nl/web/uva/sgs/nl/p/91.html', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('763', 'Tuition fees are adjusted annually, for up to date information please see www.uva.nl/isp', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'tuition fee', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('763', 'Graduates will be qualified to pursue careers in European business, law practice and public service, whether in their home country or in Brussels, Luxembourg or Strasbourg or other cities. The programme also provides a strong basis for those seeking ', 'to do a PhD in any of the various fields of European law.', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('763', 'The curriculum allows students to choose between institutional and substantive law, both of which include a large number of electives. Students may also decide to use their 30 credits for electives to specialise in a certain specific policy area of E', 'U law, for example European Environmental Law.\nCompulsory courses add up to 20 credits. With the compulsory thesis of 10 credits, this leaves 30 credits for electives.\n', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('763', 'The Master"s programme in European Union Law at the UvA is known as one of the best in the world. It attracts around 100 students annually from some 30 different countries.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'international', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('763', 'The curriculum allows students to choose between institutional and substantive law, both of which include a large number of electives. Students may decide to use their 30 EC for electives to specialise in a certain specific policy area of EU law, for', ' example European Environmental Law. Compulsory courses, including thesis add up to 30 EC. This leaves 30 EC for electives. These courses must be related to this Master"s curriculum. A maximum of 10 EC may be obtained from approved internships. \n\n', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('763', 'seminar and lectures', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'instruction modes', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('763', 'The European Union is by far the most developed international organisation in the world. It even has constitutional qualities, meaning that it is developing into a political community of its own. The EU"s relentless evolution produces new legal probl', 'ems and solutions almost every day, as a result of which it always remains a fresh subject in legal research and practice. The EUs development follows two channels: substantive and institutional/constitutional. \n', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('764', 'Tuition fees are adjusted annually. For up-to-date information, please see www.uva.nl/isp', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'tuition fee', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('764', 'This track offers a set of courses on subjects that will prepare graduates for careers in the legal service divisions of modern European companies, international business law practices, the public administrations of European Union institutions or Mem', 'ber State ministries dealing with European business law.', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('764', 'The Master"s programme in International and European Law is aimed at students who are planning a career in international law or European law.\n\nThe programme seeks to develop an understanding of the theory and practice of international and European la', 'w.The teaching methods and evaluations focus on developing writing, analytical and communication skills, as well as knowledge of Black Letter Law. To this end, greater emphasis is placed on written and oral assignments instead of traditional exams.', 'NULL', 'website', 'international', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('764', 'The track follows a coherent set of strongly interrelated, and therefore compulsory, courses which prepare the graduate students for legal service in a modern European company, in international private practice or in any EU institution and in the pub', 'lic administration of Member States dealing with business regulation. Lectures in the Capita Selecta course, which deals with the EU directives (Telecoms, Energy, Banking, etc.), are taught by faculty of the Amsterdam Law School and guest lecturers. ', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('764', 'This track focuses on the European public regulatory framework for doing business in the EU. The European treaties define the rights and obligations of business and individuals in terms of the free movement of employed persons, goods, services and ca', 'pital across the EU. Common EU policies operate to support these freedoms, including competition rules and rules governing good corporate governance.\n', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('765', 'Tuition fees are adjusted annually. For up-to-date information, please see www.uva.nl/isp', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'tuition fee', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('765', 'Graduates of the International Trade and Investment Law programme have a strong foundation for a career as a legal adviser or for further post-graduate study in international economic law. Students interested in pursuing a PhD in the field of Europea', 'n law will also have a solid basis on which to build an academic career.\n\n', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('765', 'A significant part of the study programme concerns the Geneva-based World Trade Organisation. The WTO provides the legal framework for the multilateral trading system for goods and services, including its advanced system of dispute resolution with a ', 'large and developing body of case law. WTO agreements  go beyond traditional market access issues into the realm of international legal harmonisation to consider intellectual property rights and international product and food safety standards. \n\n', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('765', 'Please see:\nhttp://studiegids.uva.nl/web/uva/sgs/en/p/847_92569.html', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('765', 'International trade and investment are driving forces in the world economy and its increasing global interdependence. This track focuses on the international legal rules of conduct that govern these economic relations for states and regions. ', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'international', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('765', 'The first semester deals with aspects of the WTO institutional and dispute settlement system as well as the core International and European Law substantive trading system. The second semester introduces the study of international investment law. This', ' track consists of 50 credits for core courses and 10 credits vor a Master"s thesis. Please see the course catalogue for a detailed description of the programme: http://studiegids.uva.nl/web/uva/sgs/en/p/847_92569.html', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('765', 'seminars and lectures', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'instruction modes', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('766', 'Tuition fees are adjusted annually, for up to date information please see www.uva.nl/isp', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'tuition fee', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('766', 'This track is designed to prepare graduates for an international career in European or international institutions, international business, law firms, goverment departments or non govermental organisations. For those who have obtained a Bachelor"s in ', 'law at the UvA, the completion of the programme results in "civil effect" in the Netherlands, meaning it gives access to the Dutch bar and magistracy. \n\n', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('766', 'Please see:  http://studiegids.uva.nl/web/uva/sgs/en/p/811_92561.html', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl');
INSERT INTO `program_links` (`program_id`, `summary1`, `summary2`, `summary3`, `type`, `subject`, `weblink`) VALUES
('766', 'The Master"s programme in International and European Law is aimed at students who are planning a career in international law or European law.\n\nThe programme consists of two components, international law and European law, which share a number of manda', 'tory courses. There are also a number of optional courses. This structure allows for specialisation in either of the components, while taking into account their common foundation. The programme seeks to develop an understanding of the theory and pr', 'NULL', 'website', 'international', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('766', 'The Public International Law curriculum provides students with a broad knowledge of general international law. In addition to the general compulsory courses of the Master, this track has two compulsory courses: Sources and foundations of internationa', 'l law (5 EC) and  State Responsibility in International Law (5 EC). The wide variety of elective courses allows students to specialise in particular areas of public international law such as human rights law, humanitarian law/the law or armed conflic', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('766', 'The Public International Law track aims to advance research and writing skills and to involve students in the practical application of international law. This may be accomplished through enrolment in the Amsterdam International Law Clinic, the Intern', 'ational Law in Domestic Courts project or one of the international moot court competitions in which the University participates. \n\n', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('766', 'lectures and seminars', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'instruction modes', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('768', 'In de bachelor en de aansluitende master wordt opgeleid tot fiscaal jurist en kun je gaan werken bij de belastingdienst, bij een belastingadvieskantoor of als zelfstandig belastingadviseur.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('769', 'European Union in a Global Order provides students with a theoretical and empirical understanding of the EU"s external relations. The programme deals with the idea of a double movement, with a dual focus on internal determination of EU"s external rel', 'ations and actions and on the impact of global developments, challenges and threats on foreign policy-making at the European and Member State level.', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('769', 'European External Relations: A Theoretical Perspective; EUGO Research Project; The EU and Asia; The EU and the Developing World; EU-US Relations: Politics and Policy.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('769', 'Lectures, seminars, study visits, independent research', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'instruction modes', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('769', 'Tuition fees are adjusted annually, for up to date information please see www.uva.nl/isp', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'tuition fee', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('769', 'This programme starts in September. The curriculum consists of one core course, two electives and a research project. The choice of courses is subject to the approval of the academic adviser. \n\nFor more information on the curriculum, please visit our', ' website.', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('769', 'The Master"s programme European Union in a Global Order prepares students for academic and professional positions in a variety of sectors, including: \n\n-academia (a PhD trajectory being a logical next step in an academic career),\n-government institut', 'ions,\n-European institutions,\n-NGOs,\n-advisory bodies / (foreign policy) think tanks,\n-journalism.', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('779', 'Operations Research is a field of study of applied analytical methods for decision making in logistical business environments.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('779', 'Advanced Deterministic Operations Research (10 EC), \nAdvanced Stochastic Operations Research (10 EC),\nOperations Research Cases 2 (5 EC),\nThesis (15 EC).\nYou have the opportunity to choose between a study programme with or without an internship. For ', 'more information about the courses 2011-2012, please see www.coursecatalogue.uva.nl.', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
