('780', 'International Relations provides students with a thorough academic grounding in International Relations (IR). It is based on a broad and interdisciplinary view of IR and explores the political, economic and social dynamics of global and regional inte', 'gration and disintegration. It seeks to promote an understanding of developments by exposing students to different perspectives and methodologies.', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('780', 'Adv. IPE; Africa and the IPE System; US Foreign Policy; EU External Relations; EU-US Relations; Global Civil Society; Global Migration; Globalism, Terrorism and the Israeli-Palestinian Conflict; New Forces in IR; Public International Law; The EU and ', 'Asia; The EU and the Developing World; The Politics of Human Rights and Conflict Resolution; Transnational Social Movements and Global Justice.', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('780', 'Lectures and seminars, individual tutoring, specialisation courses, research project, workshops.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'instruction modes', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('780', 'Tuition fees are adjusted annually, for up to date information please see www.uva.nl/isp', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'tuition fee', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('780', 'The Master"s programme in International Relations is designed for:\n\n-those who require a basis for a PhD programme in international relations; \n-those who are considering a career that requires independent research; \n-or those who wish to work for an', ' international policy-making organisation.', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('780', 'This programme starts in September. The curriculum consists of one core course, several elective courses and a research project. Fulfilling the requirements should take one year of full-time study. \n\nThe research project (30 ECTS credits) consists of', ' a seminar, primary and secondary research and a written thesis. The final Master"s thesis is a report on research carried out by the student as part of the research project. \n\nFor more information on the curriculum, please visit our website.', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('784', 'Je wordt opgeleid tot leerkracht op een basisschool in Amsterdam of een andere grote stad. Naast het lesgeven zul je door je expertise ook altijd betrokken zijn bij de leerlingzorg of de onderwijsvernieuwing binnen de school. ', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('785', 'The Biblical Studies track of the Religious Studies Master offers a wide range of courses, covering The Hebrew Bible and the New Testament, Jewish literature from the Second Temple Period and the Early Rabbinic Period Early Christian literature', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('785', 'The Master"s programme in Biblical Studies yields 60 ECTS credits: 42 credits for core courses and electives and 18 credits for a Master"s thesis', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('785', 'Seminars and tutorials with supervision by specialists devoted to the in-depth study of a variety of topics. Supervised individual research resulting in a thesis. All classes are taught in small groups, with a maximum of 20 students.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'instruction modes', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('785', 'Tuition fees are adjusted annually, for up to date information please see www.uva.nl/isp', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'tuition fee', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('785', 'The master"s programme in Biblical Studies prepares students for a career in teaching, journalism or any of the other writing professions, as well as for an advisory or managerial position in a public organisation or government institution, and at th', 'e academic level in any of the diverse fields of research or general education, particularly where the study of the Bible is involved.\n\nDutch students wishing to become first-degree teachers can join the two-year MA in Education at the ILO. ', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('786', 'The specialisation Political Communication addresses issues at the core of our democracies. It provides an understanding of the role and significance of media, journalism and information in shaping public opinion.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('786', 'Journalism and the Media (12 EC) and Citizens and Public Opinion (12 EC) and a method course (6 EC) during the first semester. In the second semester, students complete two elective modules of 6 EC each and write a Master"s thesis (18 EC). Students m', 'ust obtain a total of 60 credits to be awarded the degree.', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('786', 'Lecturers, research, written work, presentations and a thesis.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'instruction modes', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
