('805', 'Urban Sociology studies the spatial and social mobility of the urban population, the rise and decline of urban lifestyles and subcultures, and the ever changing social relations between individuals and groups in urban settings. It looks at how urbani', 'tes deal with public and private domains. It is characterized by specific approaches, focusing on sociological-historical research and ethnography.', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
