('807', 'Knowledge of and insight into theories and concepts as they have been developed in the field of addiction studies; knowledge of and insight into an interdisciplinary approach to various topics in the field of addiction studies; knowledge of and insig', 'ht into the complexity of social problems associated with addiction treatment.', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('807', 'Historical overview of addiction, an examination of international issues of addiction for social and health care systems; cross-cultural comparisons of alcohol and drug treatment systems; and comparison treatment models; treatment barriers for the of', 'ten overlapping populations of intravenous drug users, people with HIV/AIDS, adolescents, members of minority communities.', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('807', 'Lectures, seminars, discussion groups, practical assignments and individual tutoring.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'instruction modes', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('807', 'Substance abuse and its accompanying health and social problems are increasing around the world with consequences for the individual and for society as a whole. Addiction is not a new problem, but the approach to this phenomenon differs widely amongs', 't governments. The concept of addiction brings to the forefront social, medical and moral questions. What defines good treatment and are there cultural differences? There is a dire need for empirical knowledge and theoretical insights into addiction ', 'NULL', 'website', 'socio-economic contribution', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
