('812', 'The course will last four weeks, starting July 4 and ending July 28. The modules are from 9:30 am to 3:30 pm, Monday through Thursday. Fridays are reserved for literature reading, individual research activities, and travel. \nEach week a different ins', 'tructor leads a module on her or his subject. In the afternoon during week 2 and 3, the programme consists of two tracks. \n   \n', 'NULL', 'website', 'instruction modes', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('812', 'Modules:\n\n    * Sexuality, Society, and Culture: An Introduction\n(Niko Besnier)\n    * Sex(work) and the City\n      (Mirjam Schieveld, Laurens Buijs, Other lecturers)\n    * The HIV/AIDS Epidemic Contextualized   (Graeme Reid)\n    * Young Sexualities  ', ' (Deevia Bhana)\n    * Sexuality in Art and Media   (Robert Sember)\n    * Politics of Sex Work   (Elizabeth Bernstein)\n    * Seminar in Proposal Development (Track 2)  (Diane di Mauro)\n    * Sexuality and the Body   (Rebecca Jordan-Young)\n\n', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
