('825', 'Graduates of the Computer Science programme have a combination of knowledge and skills that are highly marketable in today"s workplace. Students go on to join research groups and pursue PhDs or take on similar positions in industry or commerce, where', ' their independence and inquisitive approach are valued and rewarded. Many students complete their PhD in Amsterdam. Examples of other employers include commercial banks and small and large computer and systems companies.', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('829', 'Tuition fees are adjusted annually, for up to date information please see www.uva.nl/isp\n\n', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'tuition fee', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('829', 'For more information about the curriculum please visit the website.\n', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('829', 'This Master"s programme will allow graduates to pursue further doctoral studies and enter the labour market in a variety of sectors, such as government institutions, NGOs, communication media, and other institutions whose social involvement requires ', 'research.', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('829', 'The Joint European Master in International Migration and Social Cohesion explores the critical elements of international migration and the incorporation of immigrants in the societies they enter. It teaches students advanced theories, techniques, and', ' methodologies in Migration Studies, so that they are able to translate societal problems into social scientific research questions and contribute to their solutions by combining insights from fundamental social theory with substantive theories.', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('829', 'For more information about the curriculum please visit the website.\n', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('833', 'Qualifying graduates for international careers in European and international institutions, international business, law firms. The programme also provides a strong writing and research basis for those seeking PhD research in the field of European Priv', 'ate Law.', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('833', 'This Masters programme offers a specialisation in European Private Law, based on a coherent set of courses on the topics at the heart of the harmonisation of private law in Europe. The elective courses (20 ECTS) offered are: European Consumer Law,', ' European Property Law, European Tort Law, Anthropology of European Private Law, Contract Law and Competition Law, European Company Law II, European Family Law I, Private Law Theory, Anglo-American Contract and Tort Law and European Insolvency Law. \n', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('833', 'Lectures and seminars.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'instruction modes', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('833', 'The Amsterdam Law School only accepts English language proficiency test results that are no more than one year old at the time of application.  \n\n', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'admission', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('833', 'Tuition fees are adjusted annually. For up-to-date information, please see www.uva.nl/isp', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'tuition fee', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
