('848', 'The programme consists of three specialisation courses, one course in theory, research and GIS, and a Masters thesis, totaling 60 European credits (ECTS). \n\nFor more information on the curriculum, please visit our website.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('848', 'Graduates of Human Geography qualify as scientific researchers of socio-spatial themes. In many cases, graduates secure research positions at public organisations and private firms. Potential employers range from ministries, provinces and municipalit', 'ies to housing corporations, consultancy firms and NGOs. Other job possibilities are policy advisor, journalist, teaching geography at secondary schools (after completing the education Masters) or expert in geographical information systems. ', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('848', 'Human Geography analyses the way humans use and understand the world, the spatial differentiation and organisation of human activity and its interrelationships with the physical environment. Relevant developments are globalisation and regionalism, mi', 'gration and mobility, urbanisation and urban problems, rebalancing of natural resources and sustainable development. ', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('848', 'The programme consists of three specialisation courses, one course in theory, research and GIS, and a Masters thesis, totaling 60 European credits (ECTS). \n\nFor more information on the curriculum, please visit our website.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('849', 'Tuition fees are adjusted annually. For up-to-date information, please see www.uva.nl/isp', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'tuition fee', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('849', 'The Research Master"s programme in Art Studies provides a unique foundation for students planning to pursue a PhD degree or conduct scientific research at a research institute. It also provides a solid basis for pursuing a career in roles such as a p', 'olicy position within different cultural institutions located in Amsterdam, the Netherlands or abroad e.g. Rijksmuseum Amsterdam, Mauristhuis Den Haag, Museum Boymans van Beuningen Rotterdam and the Theater Instituut Nederland.', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('849', 'The electives can be chosen from the Master"s programmes Cultural Studies(Algemene cultuurwetenschappen), Art History, Musicology  or Theatre Studies (Theaterwetenschap). All students will attend three core courses. These provide a theoretical backgr', 'ound in Art Studies.', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('849', 'Students submit a research proposal before the start of the programme. This, along with discussions with the programme director, forms the basis for the course of study. In the research proposal students write down their ideas for the three tutorials', ', their thesis and the three electives they choose. ', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('850', 'In order to participate successfully in the scholarship of this field, students must be able to read and understand Dutch fluently. Some of the courses in this programme use English, but most of the courses use Dutch.\n\n', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'instruction modes', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('850', 'The Research Master"s in Dutch Golden Age prepares participants for a related PhD programme. It provides students with a thorough introduction to current research on Dutch history and culture, as well as the skills to allow for a successful continuat', 'ion of their studies. Upon completion of the programme, students will be able to conduct research in the rich collections related to Dutch history and art preserved in libraries, archives and museums.', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('850', 'Tuition fees are adjusted annually. For up-to-date information, please see www.uva.nl/isp', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'tuition fee', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('850', 'The programme in Dutch Golden Age Studies prepares students for postgraduate studies or a career in independant research, museums, teaching, journalism or publishing.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('851', 'Tuition fees are adjusted annually, for up to date information please see www.uva.nl/isp', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'tuition fee', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('851', 'In a world of increasing globalisation, the Master"s degree in Anthropology equips you with highly relevant skills. Increasing mobility and rapid communications mean that people from across the world are engaging with each other in new and different ', 'ways.', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('851', 'The Master"s programme consists of three stages, namely designing, conducting and writing up your research in the form of a thesis.\nThe Master"s programme comprises:\nMaster"s seminar (10 ECTS), full-time course, 8 weeks \nDesigning Fieldwork(10 ', 'ECTS), full-time course, 8 weeks  \nResearch/fieldwork (20 ECTS) \nThesis seminar, leading to the Master"s anthropology conference\nThesis (20 ECTS)\n\nFor more information on the curriculum, please visit our website.', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('851', 'The Master"s programme in Anthropology at the UvA is a broadly focused one-year Master"s programme in which you design and conduct high quality anthropological research. After completing a period of fieldwork, you are expected to write a well-argued ', 'thesis. From 2011, the programme will be available in both Dutch and English. There are no thematic limitations and the research can be conducted in the Netherlands or abroad.', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('851', 'The Master"s programme consists of three stages, namely designing, conducting and writing up your research in the form of a thesis.\nThe Master"s programme comprises:\nMaster"s seminar (10 ECTS), full-time course, 8 weeks \nDesigning Fieldwork(10 ', 'ECTS), full-time course, 8 weeks  \nResearch/fieldwork (20 ECTS) \nThesis seminar, leading to the Master"s anthropology conference\nThesis (20 ECTS)', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('855', 'Students have knowledge of the influence of culture on the well-being and health of children and they become acquainted with the child"s perspective on health and health care. They have been introduced to qualitative research methods adapted to child', 'ren, and to research in specific fields such as the urban child, children and medicine, and children and HIV/AIDS.', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('855', 'The adult-child dichotomy deconstructed; cross cultural perspectives on child development and child learning; cultural determinants of child health; infant death; children; health agency; children and chronic illness; child refugees; the urban jungle', '; ADHD; ethnographic encounters with children, child to child approaches as a form of health education.', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('855', 'Each half-day session consists of a lecture and discussion, followed by individual and group assignments.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'instruction modes', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('855', 'Health is a key factor in the socio-economic sustainable development of individuals and their community. Children form an important segment and  hold an important place in the household economies of developing countries. The program provides students', ' with tools to contribute to the solution of priority health problems of children in their own countries. Students gain insights into the social, cultural and gender dimensions of health care interventions targeted at children.', 'NULL', 'website', 'socio-economic contribution', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('855', 'This module is an intensive course with a duration of two weeks. It brings together participants with a social science and medical background. During these two weeks students gain specialist knowledge in the field of children and health. They gain kn', 'owledge of theoretic approaches, concepts and qualitative research methods that they can apply in their home country. By applying the acquired knowledge and by sharing their expertise participants will strengthen the organizations functioning.', 'NULL', 'website', 'sustainable strengthening', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('855', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'brochure', 'http://amma.socsci.uva.nl/flyers-2010/children%20health%20and%20well%20being%20flyer.pdf'),
('855', 'The executive courses are organised for health and health-related professionals and/or social scientists and taught in English. The (inter)national participants will be exposed to the latest thinking in medical anthropology and will be enabled to dis', 'cuss and exchange ideas. Groups are small. Teaching style is interactive.', 'NULL', 'website', 'instruction modes', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('855', 'The short courses are part of the accredited master"s curriculum, guaranteeing that the highest academic and practical professional standards are maintained. ', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('855', 'The AMMA is meant for social scientists in multidisciplinary research projects in the field of health and health care, and for physicians and other professionals of health care, such as Departments of Public Health and programs for prevention. The pr', 'ogram is also useful for social scientists who wish to specialise in medical anthropology, as part of their PhD program planning and for academic staff of European universities planning to develop courses and/or research in medical anthropology. ', 'NULL', 'website', 'characteristics', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('855', 'The AMMA is meant for social scientists in multidisciplinary research projects in the field of health and health care, and for physicians and other professionals of health care, such as Departments of Public Health and programs for prevention. The pr', 'ogram is also useful for social scientists who wish to specialise in medical anthropology, as part of their PhD program planning and for academic staff of European universities planning to develop courses and/or research in medical anthropology. ', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('856', 'After this course participants should be able:\n\n1. To formulate some major insights from and approaches in cross cultural psychology and psychiatry;\n2. To discuss the contributions of medical anthropology to the field of psychology and psychiatry; \n3', '. To discuss the implications of insights from the social sciences for therapeutic interventions;\n4. To summarize current debates in the borderland between the three disciplines. \n', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('856', 'Epidemiology of Psychiatric Disease in Different Cultures; Culture and Personality; Culture-bound Syndromes; Psychoanalytic Perspectives; Symbolic Healing; Culture and Schizophrenia/Depression/Trauma.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('856', 'Each half-day session consists of a lecture and discussion, followed by individual and group assignments.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'instruction modes', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('856', 'Health is a key factor in the socio-economic sustainable development of individuals, their community and populations. Mental health is a neglected field in health development whereas problems abound, especially in areas of conflict and poverty. This ', 'program provides students with insight in the relationship between culture and psychological and psychiatric phenomena and enhances their ability to contribute to culture-sensitive therapeutic interventions. ', 'NULL', 'website', 'socio-economic contribution', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('856', 'This is an intensive course with a duration of two weeks. It brings together participants with a social science and medical background. During these two weeks students gain specialist knowledge in the field of culture, psychology and psychiatry. They', ' gain knowledge of theoretic approaches and concepts and of qualitative research methods. By applying the acquired skills and by sharing their expertise with other professionals, participants will strengthen the organizations functioning. ', 'NULL', 'website', 'sustainable strengthening', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
