('858', 'The AMMA is meant for social scientists in multidisciplinary research projects in the field of health and health care, and for physicians and other professionals of health care, such as Departments of Public Health and programs for prevention. The pr', 'ogram is also useful for social scientists who wish to specialise in medical anthropology, as part of their PhD program planning and for academic staff of European universities planning to develop courses and/or research in medical anthropology. ', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('859', 'The Undergraduate Certificate Programme in Social Sciences is for international exchange students. Students should have at least two years of academic background in relevant fields.\n\nOnly for some specific Master programmes there are exchange agreeme', 'nts on Master"s level. These students are officially administered in the Undergraduate Certificate Programme but enroll in the courses of the Master"s programme.', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('859', 'The programme introduces students to the following fields:\n\nAsian Societies and Cultures \nConflict, Cultural Diversity and the Law \nCulture and Modernity \nDevelopment and Planning \nDutch Society and Culture \nEthnicity, Migration and', ' Nationalism \nEuropean Society and Culture \nGender, Sexuality and Society \nInternational Relations and Globalisation \nMedia, Communication and Film \nPolitics, Governance and Democracy ', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('859', 'Seminars and lectures.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'instruction modes', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('860', 'To gain knowledge of the American legal system in particular, and legal theory in general, through a comparative and international perspective; familiarize themselves with the multifaceted aspects of the legal profession through visits to various nat', 'ional and international institutions; focus on societal and cultural topics that influence the law and the legal profession in todays world.', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('860', 'Law & Legal; European Union Law; Globalisation & Islam; Argumentation Theory; Mediation in Conflicts; Islamic Law; Public International Law; Conflict and Negotiation; Social Trends, Social Problems and Social Policies in the Netherlands; United Natio', 'ns Incorporated; Communication in Conflict Situations; European Integration.', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('860', 'Seminars and lectures.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'instruction modes', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('861', 'Potential employers include international law firms that advice in areas such as cross-border mergers and takeovers, government departments dealing with labour issues (including the Ministry of Social Affairs and the Labour Inspection), trade unions ', 'and (non-)governmental organisations such as the International Labour Organisation and the European Union institutions. Obviously, the Master"s is an excellent first step for an academic career in international and European labour law.', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('861', 'The programme is unique in its scope: worldwide, only two universities offer a comparable Master, although their approach and content are very different from the Amsterdam programme, which is the only programme solely devoted to the study of labour l', 'aw.\n', 'NULL', 'website', 'characteristics', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('861', 'Please see http://studiegids.uva.nl/web/uva/sgs/en/p/1167.html', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('861', 'The Master"s programme in International and European Labour Law is a specialised graduate programme designed to study labour law in it"s broadest sense. It is unique in its sort and a response to the great demand for specialised labour laywers.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'international', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('861', 'The approach is not only international in the sense that European law (e.g. the EU charter, directives) and the international organisations as the ILO are subject of analysis, but also multi-national: one of the goals of the programme is to go beyond', ' the national approach that is common to most juridical curricula. This goal is achieved by giving you the opportunity to study, compare and discuss the various national approaches to labour law that exist in the world, especially in Europe.\n\n', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('861', 'The programme consists of 60 European Credits (ECTS) and will cover one full academic year. The year is divided into two semesters (a summer/autumn semester and a winter/spring semester), containing two periods each. All courses are 5 European Credit', 's (ECTS) each will be taught during a full block of 7 weeks. Exams will take place after each block. \nThe optional courses are offered by the Amsterdam Law School. Other optional courses can be taken after the approval of the programme director.', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('861', 'EU: about 1,720\nnon-EU: 12,000', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'tuition fee', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('862', 'Students from any major are welcome to apply but at least one class in the social sciences is required.  A general interest in the social sciences and an open mind are necessary.  ', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'admission', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('862', 'There will be daily (guest) lectures and/or excursions.  Students will be expected to complete all required reading for every class, complete small writing assignments, and a short presentation. ', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'instruction modes', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('862', 'The three-week program will consist of lectures, introduction to Dutch classes, guest lectures and site visits within and outside of Amsterdam.  The course will be led and moderated by Prof. Dr. Leon Deben, a professor emeritus of Urban Sociology at ', 'the University of Amsterdam.  He is an expert on Amsterdam and has worked for many years with international groups of students.\n\n\n', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('862', 'The Netherlands is known for its pragmatic solutions to every day problems.  Students will not only explore the policies behind issues such as immigration, drugs and sex work but will also look at their social implications in Amsterdam.  \n\n Through t', 'his program students will gain a better understanding of the social policies and concept of pragmatic tolerance within The Netherlands.  They will also have a chance to explore Amsterdam and surrounding areas.   ', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('862', 'The three-week program will consist of lectures, introduction to Dutch classes, guest lectures and site visits within and outside of Amsterdam.  Students will explore the following types of topics: immigration, urban planning, sex work, same sex marr', 'iage, drugs, euthanasia. \n', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('862', 'Application consists of: \n\n    * Application form\n    * Relevant transcripts/diplomas\n    * Letter of Recommendation Statement of Motivation \n', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'admission', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('862', 'Tuition includes:\n\n    * All reading materials\n    * All site visits\n    * Lunch on class days\n    * Welcome and Farewell dinners\n\nTuition Fee: 1400 Euro\nHousing: ~450 Euro\nPlease see website for details', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'tuition fee', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('862', 'This programme is great to learn more about the Netherlands and its social policies. You will be in an international learning environment and have a combination of lectures, research, discussion and excursions. ', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'international', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('863', 'The programme starts with a comprehensive core course that discusses the theoretical foundations of IDS, topical debates in the field of IDS and its applications in policy and practice. Students follow a course in research methodology and one electiv', 'e course. The second semester comprises fieldwork and thesis writing. The thesis will be based on an independent research project undertaken in a developing country. \n\nFor more information on the curriculum, please visit our website.', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('863', 'This programme is intended for students interested in pursuing careers in various areas of the development sector. Both international organisations and national organisations working on international development issues actively seek candidates with a', 'n academic background in international development studies. The Master"s programme also provides a valuable foundation for students planning to continue their studies in order to teach or conduct research in development issues.', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('863', 'The Master"s programme in International Development Studies provides students with a thorough background in contemporary theories and debates on international development, as well as more specific insights into key themes within the international dev', 'elopment sector.', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('863', 'The programme starts with a comprehensive core course that discusses the theoretical foundations of IDS, topical debates in the field of IDS and its applications in policy and practice. Students follow a course in research methodology and one electiv', 'e course. The second semester comprises fieldwork and thesis writing. The thesis will be based on an independent research project undertaken in a developing country. \n\nFor more information on the curriculum, please visit our website.', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('865', 'Het arbeidsmarktperspectief voor studenten Politieke Theorie en Politiek Gedrag is zonder meer gunstig te noemen. Een heel klein deel van de algemene politicologen gaat de wetenschap in om zich daar via promotieonderzoek te specialiseren of om zich t', 'e ontwikkelen tot publieksintellectueel.', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('865', 'De master bestaat uit een specialisatiemodule, twee werkcolleges naar keuze en een afstudeerproject. \n\nVoor meer informatie over het curriculum, ga naar onze website.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('866', 'Students with a Master"s degree in Urban and Regional Planning can expect enhanced career opportunities in the public domain as well as in the private sectors.\n\nThere are a number of possible employers in the public domain e.g. ministries, provinces ', 'or municipalities while in the private sector there are opportunities in housing corporations, within real estate or research/consultancy firms for spatial issues.', 'NULL', 'website', 'job perspective', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('866', 'The Master"s programme in Urban and Regional Planning consists consists the following elements:\n\nPlanning Methodologies (6 ECTS)\nInnovatice Planning Practies (6 ECTS)\nStrategic planning (6 ECTS)\nTransport Planning (6 ECTS)\nArea Develop', 'ment and Real Estate (6 ECTS)\nMethodes & techniques (thesis preparation) (6 ECTS)\nThesis (24 ECTS)\nPlease note that the curriculum is still under construction. Dor up-to-date information on the curriculum, please visit our website.\n', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('482_parttime', 'Our goal is to give students a high-quality business and management education to enable them to develop into effective leaders. Leaders who convey what our MBA stands for: internationally oriented and with a strong understanding of the importance of ', 'a genuine personal approach.', 'NULL', 'website', 'objectives', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('482_parttime', 'Amsterdam Leadership Programme, HRM, Operations & Process Management,Quantative Methods, International Study Trip, Marketing Strategy, Financial Accounting, Corporate Strategy, Thesis.\nFor more information about the courses 2011-2012, please see www.', 'studeren.uva.nl/english_mba.', 'NULL', 'website', 'curriculum', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('482_parttime', 'Lectures, case studies, group work, presentations.', 'NULL', 'NULL', 'website', 'instruction modes', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
('482_parttime', 'The deadline to be eligible for the early-bird tuition fee of  26,000 is March 1, 2012.\nThe deadline to receive a 5% discount if you pay your tuition fee at once is April 30, 2012.\nThe deadline to be eligible for the MBA Tuition Waiver Scheme is M', 'ay 31, 2012.\nTuition fees are adjusted annually. For up-to-date information, please see www.uva.nl/isp', 'NULL', 'website', 'tuition fee', 'http://studieadres.nl'),
